03:12.723 --> 03:14.425
What?

03:14.425 --> 03:17.468
You just tied me for
most friends on the
Webster Wolfpack website!

03:17.468 --> 03:20.571
(GASPS) Yay! High...

03:20.571 --> 03:21.572
Five.

03:22.403 --> 03:23.874
Not yay!

03:23.874 --> 03:27.838
I have to be
more popular than you
because I'm the popular girl.

03:27.838 --> 03:31.582
I would never rob you of
your title of dumb girl.

03:31.582 --> 03:33.614
Aw, that's sweet, Lexi.

03:34.745 --> 03:36.547
What am I supposed to do?

03:36.547 --> 03:39.350
I'm already friends with
everyone in school
who's on Wolfpack.

03:39.350 --> 03:41.452
We'll be tied forever!

03:41.452 --> 03:43.494
Are you guys
talking about Wolfpack?

03:43.494 --> 03:46.897
Because I just signed up and
I already have two friends.

03:46.897 --> 03:49.560
Three if Chyna
accepts my request.

03:49.560 --> 03:50.631
(PHONE CHIMES)

03:52.763 --> 03:53.764
Two it is.

03:54.935 --> 03:56.737
(PHONES CHIMING)

03:56.737 --> 03:58.369
(GASPS) Oh,

03:58.369 --> 04:00.741
you're both
trying to friend me!
 Wait.

04:00.741 --> 04:02.513
Lexi only wants you
to accept her

04:02.513 --> 04:04.645
so she'll have the most
Wolfpack friends.

04:04.645 --> 04:09.650
So, you guys are using me
to break a tie
in the popularity contest?

04:09.650 --> 04:11.852
Mmm.
 Cool!

04:11.852 --> 04:14.425
Used by the popular girls!

04:14.425 --> 04:17.387
I just want to
be your friend because
I like having friends.

04:17.387 --> 04:18.728
And I just want to
be your friend because

04:18.728 --> 04:22.393
I like having more friends
than she does.

04:22.393 --> 04:25.696
I'll just have to figure out
who is the better friend.

04:25.696 --> 04:28.469
You can start by each
bringing me a gift.

04:28.469 --> 04:31.001
Something that shows
how well you know me.

04:31.001 --> 04:32.373
A gift?

04:32.373 --> 04:35.606
Ooh, this will be
just like Presents Day!

04:35.606 --> 04:37.648
You mean Christmas?

04:37.648 --> 04:39.610
No, Presents Day,

04:39.610 --> 04:43.414
when we celebrate
Present Lincoln,
Present Washington...

04:43.414 --> 04:45.285
How is this like Christmas?

04:48.859 --> 04:52.563
Well, my dad tried,
but he couldn't get
his old job back.

04:52.563 --> 04:54.525
He burned all his bridges.

04:54.525 --> 04:57.598
No wonder they're so upset.
You can't just burn a bridge.

04:57.598 --> 05:00.501
People will notice
that sort of thing
on their drive to work.

05:03.604 --> 05:05.536
Hey, Dad.
Where were you?

05:05.536 --> 05:09.309
Ah! Pursuing my dream
of working in the movies.

05:09.309 --> 05:12.683
But being an usher
is not as glamorous as
I thought it would be.

05:14.685 --> 05:16.316
Now where's the remote?

05:16.316 --> 05:18.689
I don't know.
You never let me touch it.

05:20.651 --> 05:21.852
Let's see.

05:21.852 --> 05:25.626
Last time
I had the remote,
I was on the couch.

05:25.626 --> 05:27.327
See?

05:27.327 --> 05:30.531
Here are the crumbs
from the popcorn
I had for breakfast.

05:32.633 --> 05:37.608
And I remember I wanted
popcorn sauce on my popcorn.

05:40.841 --> 05:42.973
Popcorn sauce?

05:42.973 --> 05:45.075
He calls butter
"popcorn sauce."

05:45.075 --> 05:48.348
His parents wouldn't
let him say "butter" because
it has the word "butt" in it.

05:50.651 --> 05:53.724
So I looked in the popcorn
sauce compartment,

05:54.685 --> 05:56.627
and here it is!

05:57.488 --> 05:58.559
(LAUGHS)

05:58.559 --> 05:59.960
Wow, Dad,

05:59.960 --> 06:02.863
that was amazing the way
you just tracked that down.

06:02.863 --> 06:04.795
You should be
a private eye!

06:06.036 --> 06:09.500
Maybe I should.
 (LAUGHS)

06:09.500 --> 06:12.473
Totally. You're the best
investigator I know,

06:12.473 --> 06:14.044
and I'm not just
buttering you up.

06:14.044 --> 06:16.947
Chyna, watch your language.

06:16.947 --> 06:21.612
Sorry. And I'm not just
popcorn saucing you up.

06:21.612 --> 06:22.683
Better.

